  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc0\u0bb4\u0bcd 21,000 \u0bae\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baf\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "21,000 MT of Urea Fertilizer under India Loan Scheme",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Ministry of Agriculture, 21,000 metric tonnes of fertilizer will reach the country in two weeks under the Indian loan scheme.",
        "The first batch of 44,000 metric tonnes of fertilizer received under India loan assistance arrived in the country last week.",
        "The said fertilizer is currently being distributed to farmers by Sri Lanka Fertilizer Company Limited and Colombo Commercial Fertilizer Company.",
        "The Ministry of Agriculture has informed that today (18) the money required for the purchase of fuel will be given to the Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation to address the fuel crisis in fertilizer supply."
      ],
